ğŸ¯ Problem Statement

Most small and mid-size retailers rely on:
	â€¢	intuition,
	â€¢	recent sales trends,
	â€¢	or naive heuristics (e.g., yesterdayâ€™s sales = tomorrowâ€™s stock)

These approaches ignore demand patterns, seasonality, and uncertainty, resulting in:
	â€¢	frequent stockouts
	â€¢	overstocking
	â€¢	avoidable revenue loss

â¸»

ğŸ’¡ Solution

This project builds a pipeline that goes beyond prediction accuracy and focuses on business decisions:
	1.	Demand Forecasting
Uses historical sales data to predict near-term product demand using XGBoost.
	2.	Inventory Optimization
Converts predicted demand into recommended stock levels using safety-stock logic.
	3.	Cost Simulation
Quantifies the financial impact of:
	â€¢	understocking (lost sales)
	â€¢	overstocking (holding costs)
	4.	Web Application
A Streamlit-based UI allows store owners to upload sales data and receive:
	â€¢	recommended inventory levels
	â€¢	forecasted demand
	â€¢	estimated cost impact
	â€¢	downloadable results

â¸»

ğŸš€ Key Features
	â€¢	Multi-product demand forecasting
	â€¢	Time-series feature engineering (lags, rolling statistics, calendar features)
	â€¢	Machine learning model using XGBoost
	â€¢	Baseline vs ML model comparison
	â€¢	Inventory decision logic with cost assumptions
	â€¢	Interactive web interface (CSV upload â†’ results)
	â€¢	Fully deployed public web app

